post_text:
ATTENTION J-L
ATTENDANCE AT HOME GAMES

When fall sports were allowed to resume, attendance policies were also put into place. Below are attendance procedures for home games at J-L.

1. Each athlete is allowed to have two spectators in attendance.
2. A list of the spectators who are allowed to attend home games will be at the ticket table/booth.
3. If you are not on the list, you may not attend the game.
4. Cost of admission will be by donation only. Normal admission is $3 per student and $5 for adults.
5. Everyone attending must wear a mask.

Please continue to be patient as we work through this.

post_text: Since there is a possibility of football returning in the fall, there will be football practice Tuesday-Thursday next week (8th-10th) from 4:15 until 6:15. You may not stay after school for practice. If you are a Lewiston athlete, there is a bus that will return to the Joburg school. The bus leaves the Lewiston school at 3:45. There is not a bus to take athletes back home at 6:15. You will need to arrange your own ride home.

post_text:
Important JL Cardinals Cross Country Info:
- HS practice begins Wednesday August 12 from 6-8 p.m., beginning at the track.
- We will practicing in the evenings at that same time (6-8 pm) until school begins.
- Please bring the completed and signed health waiver/questionnaire to first practice (see separate FB post for a PDF) as this replaces/updates your physical from last year on file.
- PLEASE bring your own water bottle to practice as they can't be shared (will be able to refill)!
- At this time any meets/competition are "up in the air" as the "Ryan Shay 2 mile" has been cancelled already and the East Jordan Invite is likely to be cancelled also. We will keep you posted!
- At this time, MS Cross Country is unsure... We will know more by August 20 (first practices wouldn't be until school begins on August 31 though)

Thanks for your patience and can't wait to start!!
Coach DeHoog

post_text:
ATTENTION HIGH SCHOOL VOLLEYBALL

Some news to share...At this time our district is in Phase 4 which means we may only hold volleyball practice outdoors. We are allowed to begin (outdoor) practice as scheduled on Aug 12th, but the MHSAA will be making a decision on Aug 20th about whether competition will even begin for fall sports like football and volleyball.

Per Mr. Smokevich, we are in phase 4 because Oscoda County is in phase 4. Part of Oscoda county is in our school district.

post_text:
ALL J-L ATHLETES IMPORTANT POST!

If you have a students that plans on participating in sports this year, they must have a physical on file before the start of practice. This year, MHSAA is allowing students who had a physical on file last year, to fill out a "Health Questionnaire" as a substitute physical for the 2020/2021 school year.

Steps for the Health Questionnaire

1) Student must have a physical on file from 2019/2020 school yr.

2) Should not have any major changes to students health

3) Form: www.mhsaa.com. Located at the top of the website.

All other students will have to get a current physical if you did not get a physical or did not turn a physical form to the athletic office last school year.

It’s a great day to be a Cardinal!

post_text:
Thanks to the efforts of Mr. Chrencik, Mr. Proctor, and myself, along with the generosity of two local fitness centers, we have secured places for athletes to workout this summer while construction is taking place at the school. The Powerhouse in Gaylord and the Get Fit Center on Lewiston will allow our athletes to work out at each place this summer. The athletic department has taken care of the fee for the summer.

A few rules when working out at each center:
1. Inappropriate behavior will not be tolerated. Please act accordingly.
2. Workout with a partner so you have a spotter.
3. Get Fit in Lewiston requires all athletes under the age of 18 to have parents fill out a waiver to lift there.
4. Athletes may work out at anytime, not limited to the original calendar.
5. PLEASE be sure to thank the Powerhouse or Get Fit each and every time you visit!

Have a great summer!
It’s a great day to be a Cardinal!
